{
  "title": "Selection Offer",
  "story": [
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "id": "fc9a81e18752bf8a",
      "text": "A recipient of communication, however, always has the possibility to negate – be it not to continue communication, be it to subsequently, but discrepantly, select (seligieren). He can understand and reject selection offers – and nothing else is communication."
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "id": "406f6b46b2c94bb6",
      "text": "One must therefore distinguish between comprehensibility and acceptance of communications. Communications of everyday life generally seek not only intelligibility, but also acceptance of their selection offers and are pre-selected for acceptance possibilities. Already the speaker and even more so the receiver of a communication thus perform a selective function in the direction of successful reproduction of meaning. This selective treatment of communications is a mass, everyday occurrence. It can be tested by Garfinkeleien. As a permanent phenomenon of human coexistence enforced by the variation mechanism of language, it initially remains without major cultural-historical significance and almost without risk. Almost nothing depends on the acceptance or rejection in the individual case for the society itself and for its evolution. Nevertheless, here lies the evolutionary potential with respect to the selective function of evolution, namely the possibility to form independent selective mechanisms which change the conditions of selective success and adapt them to the development of the social system. Only the selective realization of the aspects of selective success of communications controls the evolution."
    },
    {
      "type": "pagefold",
      "id": "ec21eb242f1153b7",
      "text": "~"
